<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871020-0041 </DOCNO><HL> Zellars Is Asked to HeadSandamp;L Asset Disposal Agency</HL><DD> 10/20/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> GOVMTBANKS, THRIFT INSTITUTIONS (BNK) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   John Zellars, chairman and president of Georgia Federal Bank, has been asked to serve as chairman of the Federal Asset Disposition Association, a government official confirmed.    The current chairman, Roslyn Payne, has been under fire from some members of Congress for her performance and her $250,000 salary. The Associated Press reported that Mr. Zellars was invited to serve without a salary.    Mr. Zellars is currently one of 11 members of the board of the government agency that sells assets from bankrupt savings institutions taken over by the Federal Savings and Loan Insurance Corp.    The government official wouldn't discuss the situation further. Neither Ms. Payne nor Mr. Zellars could be reached for comment. </TEXT></DOC>